defaultCONCLUSION
default14. 
defaultIn short, therefore, those who promote academies and free schools in our area do not engage in debate or proper consultation with those who might be considered legitimate stake-holders, preferring to further their cause 
defaultby more underhand means including, where they feel it necessary, threat and intimidation. They also appear to be engaged in an undemocratic behind-the-scenes 'network' of dubious conflicted interests, with clear financial benefits for some at the top.
default Fina
defaultlly, posing as both more effective and efficient than local authority schools, academies and free schools 
defaultactually 
defaultappear to waste public money
default - on
default additional management/admin posts or promotion - 
defaultthat could be 
defaultbetter spent on the education of children.
default A
defaults yet, we have seen little evidence locally that academies are more effective than their local authority predecessors and counterparts. 
